🙌 Sōl Day Joy 🙌

We’re humbled and honored to have participated, in a small way, in @handsinthesoil’s 8th Annual Sōl Day 💜. 

Thanks to an invitation from the phenomenal @yd.natur 🙌—who you won’t regret taking a yoga class 🧘‍♀️ with at @thepostclimbing—we were able to help some of the families who lost homes in the Eaton Fire get to this healing, grounding, and expansive event. 

Hands in the Soil is on a mission to cultivate healthy habits and spiritual well-being through community practice. And as you can see from the photos, the day was a success 🔥.

In today’s world, nothing brings us more joy 🥰 than seeing these kinds of humans and communities rise, and we’re so thankful to have been a part of it.

